    "what_description": "Simira ecuadorensis is a species of plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is a shrub or small tree with a height of up to 10 meters, characterized by its brown and grayish-brown bark and its elliptical or ovate leaves, measuring 5-15 cm in length and 2-7 cm in width, with a pubescent underside and a cuneate base. The leaves are opposite or alternate and have a short petiole with a pubescent stalk. The inflorescence is a raceme with a length of up to 12 cm, bearing 2-4 flowers with a corolla tube of 6-8 mm and a corolla limb of 5-7 mm. The flowers are white with a yellow or red tint on the outside of the corolla tube.",
