    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Simira ecuadorensis improperly are inducing nausea due to its emetic properties, causing diarrhea due to its purgative effects, increasing heart rate as a result of its cardiac glycoside content, triggering seizures in individuals with pre-existing epilepsy due to its neurotoxic properties, and in severe cases, it can lead to a range of other adverse effects including liver and kidney damage, as well as respiratory failure. This is because Simira ecuadorensis contains compounds like simarin and other cardiac glycosides, which are toxic to the human body and can cause severe side effects when used improperly. The improper use of Simira ecuadorensis can also lead to other health complications such as arrhythmias, cardiac arrest, and even death. The toxic compounds in Simira ecuadorensis can also cause gastrointestinal upset, including nausea and diarrhea, as well as neurological symptoms such as seizures and tremors. Overall, the improper use of Simira ecuadorensis can have severe and potentially life-threatening side effects.",
